Name: wslKaliLinux
Description: Run commands inside WSL Kali Linux.
Version: 1.0

Overview:
This toolset runs commands inside the Kali Linux WSL distribution.

Commands:
- wsl_kali_start
  Start the Kali Linux WSL distro.

- wsl_kali_run
  Run a command inside Kali Linux.
  Parameters:
  - command (string, required): Command to run in Kali.
  - user (string, optional): Username inside WSL.
  - cwd (string, optional): Working directory inside WSL.
  - timeout (integer, optional): Timeout seconds.

- wsl_kali_stop
  Stop the Kali Linux WSL distro.

Usage Examples:
- wsl_kali_start
- wsl_kali_run command="ls -la"
- wsl_kali_run command="sudo apt update" user="root"
- wsl_kali_stop

Behavior Notes:
- Uses `wsl -d kali-linux` and runs via `bash -lc`.

Dependencies:
- Windows Subsystem for Linux (WSL)
- Kali Linux distribution installed in WSL
